author: benjamin

title: Everyday Magic
author: charlie
text: in my backyard,  running in my ravine,  on the side of a cliff,  wearing away the rock.   down in the harbor,  as cold as dry,  as dirty as mud,  on freshly clean glass.   feels like home,  hopping with frogs.  slimy algae surrounding a lily pad,  smells like spring turning into summer.   holding the sprayer,  washing my face.  as ordinary as waking up,  as amazing as flying.
